1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:01,208
I was in the store

2
00:00:02,625 --> 00:00:03,791
Two people came to me

3
00:00:04,541 --> 00:00:06,208
They said, Are you Aladdin? I said, Yes

4
00:00:07,541 --> 00:00:11,333
He said, Please come with us to the <i>Hisba</i> [morality police]

5
00:00:12,916 --> 00:00:13,916
I said, What is the matter?

6
00:00:14,041 --> 00:00:16,166
They said, We want to ask you some questions

7
00:00:16,958 --> 00:00:19,333
They took me and brought me to this place

8
00:00:21,583 --> 00:00:22,708
They interrogated me

9
00:00:25,166 --> 00:00:28,083
When they brought me in, I was terrified, afraid

10
00:00:28,416 --> 00:00:31,500
Because their hands were stained with the blood of innocent people

11
00:00:31,541 --> 00:00:35,333
Now I would become one of those people

12
00:00:38,958 --> 00:00:42,208
Interviewer: The two people who brought you here

13
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:44,291
Can you describe their appearance?

14
00:00:44,291 --> 00:00:47,583
And how old were they? What was their appearance?

15
00:00:48,083 --> 00:00:51,500
Were they from Mosul, based on the accent they spoke to you with?

16
00:00:51,791 --> 00:00:54,333
Or were they from the outskirts of Mosul, or from other provinces?

17
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:56,041
Or were they of other Arab nationalities?

18
00:00:57,041 --> 00:00:58,166
They were from different backgrounds

19
00:00:58,208 --> 00:01:02,916
But the two who came to me—one was from Hadar and the other from Mosul.

20
00:01:04,166 --> 00:01:06,208
So their dialect was the Moslawi dialect

21
00:01:06,708 --> 00:01:07,916
They worked in the <i>Hisba</i>

22
00:01:08,541 --> 00:01:10,166
Interviewer: Approximately how old were they?

23
00:01:11,541 --> 00:01:14,500
About 40 or 45 years old

24
00:01:15,458 --> 00:01:17,916
Yes, the two who took me

25
00:01:18,541 --> 00:01:19,958
Interviewer: How did they treat you from the moment they took you...

26
00:01:19,958 --> 00:01:21,291
until they brought you to the prison?

27
00:01:22,083 --> 00:01:24,208
Very normally

28
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:26,916
They didn’t talk to me in front of people

29
00:01:27,208 --> 00:01:29,791
They brought me and led me in here

30
00:01:30,416 --> 00:01:31,458
And they interrogated me

31
00:01:31,625 --> 00:01:33,791
Interviewer: Did they bring you on foot or by car?
Witness: No, on foot

32
00:01:34,583 --> 00:01:37,416
Because the distance is short, about 10 minutes on foot

33
00:01:38,208 --> 00:01:39,791
Interviewer: Was one of them holding you?

34
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:42,458
Or were you handcuffed?

35
00:01:42,666 --> 00:01:46,208
No, I walked in front of them and they were behind me, armed

36
00:01:47,291 --> 00:01:50,208
Interviewer: So they escorted you without anyone holding you

37
00:01:50,291 --> 00:01:51,666
No, no, they didn’t do anything to me

38
00:01:51,958 --> 00:01:53,583
They just told me they wanted to ask me questions

39
00:01:54,166 --> 00:01:56,791
Interviewer: When they took you to the prison gate

40
00:01:56,916 --> 00:01:58,166
Did those same men go in with you?

41
00:01:58,208 --> 00:01:59,916
Or did they hand you over to other people?

42
00:02:00,083 --> 00:02:02,583
They brought me here and then handed me over to other people
